data.title: Regis Students Recognized for Academic Excellence on Fall 2023 Dean's List
data.meta_description: Regis College has announced those students named to the university’s Dean’s List for the fall 2023 semester.
data.text:
Regis College has proudly announced those students named to the university’s fall 2023 Dean's List recognizing their outstanding academic achievements. To earn a spot on the Dean's List, Regis sophomores, juniors, seniors, and professional studies students must have a GPA of 3.5 or higher; first-year students must have a GPA of 3.25 or higher. Additional criteria can be found in Regis' Academic Catalog.

Founded by the Sisters of St. Joseph nearly a century ago, Regis challenges, inspires, and supports students who are driven by passion, purpose, and a pursuit to positively impact the world within a learning community that embraces inclusivity and innovation and builds strong character, confidence, and careers.

Regis congratulates the following students named to the fall 2023 Dean’s List:
